Attached is a summary of objections we discussed yesterday.

In summary, we acquired CardConnect at the beginning of June to accomplish the following goals:

1) 	Provide a safe and secure gateway (and ultimately processing) for our software partners, many of whom were boarding
merchants with CardConnect.
2) 	Capitalize on their existing reseller program
3) 	Strengthen our ongoing litigation regarding their theft of trade secrets

Since the acquisition, we’ve identified several critical issues that have dramatically impacted our ability to achieve these
goals, including:

* CardConnect sales partners have, to date, been unable to integrate with Shift4 products
* CardConnect failed in every aspect of boarding and support for their reseller partners
* CardConnect’s sales partners have been so dissatisfied that every partner has demanded to be released
* CardConnect's reseller residuals are paid almost entirely to 2 partners, one of which we terminated with CAUSE
* CardConnect was processing significantly less volume than we were led to believe

We have a call scheduled later today to discuss these and other open items regarding CardConnect. Our goal is to get
on the otherside of these issues so we can integrate those partners (software and reseller) that want to be integrated.

Thanks

Taylor Orgeron | Chief Sales Officer
